</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,1602,1703]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Listed in Cardoso’s 
<collectingCountry box="[392,493,1602,1628]" name="Portugal" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Portugal</collectingCountry>
Spider Catalogue (2009b), but incorrectly identified. The specimens belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wunderlich)" baseAuthorityName="Wunderlich" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[151,632,1640,1666]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Palliduphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cadiziensis">
<emphasis box="[151,466,1640,1665]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Palliduphantes cadiziensis</emphasis>
(Wunderlich)
</taxonomicName>
(see there). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[780,1060,1640,1665]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Palliduphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cernuus">
<emphasis box="[780,1060,1640,1665]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Palliduphantes cernuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
